The Golden Age of Radio: Program 10 - January, 1971 - Goodman Ace

infos.info: The series began on KMBC-Kansas City, Missouri in 1930 and remained there for a year before CBS gave it a thirteen-week tryout near the end of 1931. In 1932 the show found a sponsor in Lavoris, and its long run with CBS and NBC was under way. - Source: Jim Cox, Historical Dictionary of American Radio Soap Operas, p.74. - The show was in 15 and 30 minute versions. - In 1944, the series was also known as ' Mr. Ace and Jane' - 1948 version: Mr.Ace &amp Jane
